The provincial education department says more than half a million pupils met the midnight deadline to register online. JOHANNESBURG - The process to place grade one and grade eight pupils at Gauteng schools for the 2019 academic year has started. The provincial Education Department says that more than half a million pupils met the midnight deadline to register online. Parents will be informed about where their children have been placed in July. The department's spokesperson Steve Mabona says: “Now that they have applied, they need to submit the documents at the schools. All the schools you applied to, you need to submit documents until 5 June. From there we will be focusing on placements.” (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)